"signal_description": "The given SIGNAL query is designed to extract several pieces of information from the 'defaultview-225' table. Firstly, it selects the 'Inv. Company Code Text' column. Then, it calculates the total 'Inv. Converted USD Amount' and labels it as 'Invoice Amount in $'. It also counts the number of 'Inv. Accounting Document Number' entries and labels it as 'No. of Invoices'. The query calculates the average 'Payment Block Rate' and labels it as 'Avg. Payment Block Rate in %'. It also calculates the average number of days from 'Inv. Posting Document Date' to 'Last Inv. Item Due Date' and labels it as 'Avg. days from posting to due date'. The query then calculates the percentage of 'Inv. Accounting Document Number' entries where 'Inv. Creation User Type' is 'System' and the event name matches 'Post Invoice', and labels it as 'Automatic Invoice Posting in %'. It also calculates the percentage of 'Inv. Accounting Document Number' entries where the event name matches any string containing 'update', and labels it as 'Change Rate in %'. Finally, it calculates the percentage of 'Inv. Accounting Document Number' entries where the event name occurs more than once, and labels it as 'Rework Rate in %'. The query only considers rows where 'Last Inv. Item Clearing Date' is NULL and 'Last Inv. Item Due Date' is earlier than the current date. The results are grouped by 'Inv. Company Code Text' and ordered by 'Invoice Amount in $' in descending order."
